1
00:00:32,281 --> 00:00:36,953
THE PRACTICAL GUIDE TO LOVE

2
00:00:50,841 --> 00:00:52,051
- Hey.
- Mom!

3
00:00:56,597 --> 00:00:57,640
Oh, my.

4
00:00:58,140 --> 00:01:00,393
Are you okay? Are you hurt?

5
00:01:00,476 --> 00:01:02,520
Oh, gosh! What do I do?

6
00:01:02,728 --> 00:01:04,021
I'm so sorry!

7
00:01:04,564 --> 00:01:06,232
No, it's fine.

8
00:01:06,607 --> 00:01:08,943
Nice to meet you. Hello.

9
00:01:10,987 --> 00:01:11,988
Huh?

10
00:01:14,156 --> 00:01:15,700
Could we get some more water?

11
00:01:15,783 --> 00:01:17,493
- Sure.
- And a beer.

12
00:01:18,703 --> 00:01:20,288
Hey! You always eat at my restaurant.

13
00:01:20,496 --> 00:01:21,581
Ma'am!

14
00:01:34,927 --> 00:01:38,598
THE PRACTICAL GUIDE TO LOVE
EPISODE 7

15
00:01:43,019 --> 00:01:46,439
You should've called before coming.
What about the restaurant?

16
00:01:46,522 --> 00:01:50,151
I thought I should give you
these side dishes while they were fresh.

17
00:01:52,320 --> 00:01:54,947
I'll just put these away and get going.

18
00:01:55,072 --> 00:01:58,784
No, you just came here. Stay for a bit.

19
00:01:59,118 --> 00:02:01,162
Let me drive you home. I'll be right back.

20
00:02:03,414 --> 00:02:05,791
Here. Have a seat.

21
00:02:05,875 --> 00:02:08,044
I'm so sorry for interrupting your date.

22
00:02:08,127 --> 00:02:09,545
Not at all.

23
00:02:10,296 --> 00:02:12,340
What's your name?

24
00:02:13,049 --> 00:02:15,593
I'm Lee Ui-yeong.

25
00:02:15,676 --> 00:02:17,219
- Ui-yeong?
- Yeah.

26
00:02:17,303 --> 00:02:19,347
I've known you for so long,
but never your name!

27
00:02:19,680 --> 00:02:23,100
You always come with your boyfriend,
no, friend.

28
00:02:23,434 --> 00:02:26,604
You work at a hotel, and you love soju.

29
00:02:27,021 --> 00:02:29,273
You can drink two...
No, one bottle of soju.

30
00:02:29,774 --> 00:02:30,775
Right.

31
00:02:31,150 --> 00:02:32,443
She remembers everything!

32
00:02:32,526 --> 00:02:35,363
I pick things up
by eavesdropping on the tables

33
00:02:35,446 --> 00:02:36,906
to see if anyone needs anything.

34
00:02:37,323 --> 00:02:40,660
You mentioned recently
that you were going on a blind date.

35
00:02:40,785 --> 00:02:43,287
Is that where you met Tae-seop?

36
00:02:46,123 --> 00:02:47,708
Yeah, I did.

37
00:02:47,792 --> 00:02:50,294
What a coincidence!

38
00:02:50,378 --> 00:02:52,088
How long have you been dating?

39
00:02:52,171 --> 00:02:54,465
Well, we...

40
00:02:54,840 --> 00:02:57,134
We're not official yet.

41
00:02:57,218 --> 00:03:01,347
It's also my first time here.
He needed to get his glasses.

42
00:03:01,597 --> 00:03:02,640
I see.

43
00:03:03,432 --> 00:03:05,101
It's okay, you guys aren't kids.

44
00:03:05,184 --> 00:03:06,644
I'm all for this.

45
00:03:06,727 --> 00:03:08,145
You two don't have time to waste.

46
00:03:08,229 --> 00:03:11,941
You should really get to know him,
you know, in every way.

47
00:03:12,024 --> 00:03:13,067
Sorry?

48
00:03:13,651 --> 00:03:15,319
Are you ready to go?

49
00:03:15,403 --> 00:03:17,571
I'll drop off Ui-yeong, then you.

50
00:03:23,285 --> 00:03:25,329
You two can sit in the front.

51
00:03:25,413 --> 00:03:26,747
No, you can sit in the front!

52
00:03:26,831 --> 00:03:28,791
- No, I prefer the back.
- What?

53
00:03:29,417 --> 00:03:30,793
You can get in the front!

54
00:03:33,462 --> 00:03:35,089
It's fine. Just sit in the front.

55
00:03:44,890 --> 00:03:47,309
You two look great together.

56
00:03:50,438 --> 00:03:52,857
It's not safe to sit like that, Mom.

57
00:03:56,777 --> 00:04:00,698
Did I mention you two look great together?

58
00:04:01,365 --> 00:04:02,867
Oh, yeah.

59
00:04:03,576 --> 00:04:07,163
You've been saying that the whole ride.

60
00:04:08,789 --> 00:04:10,374
My gosh!

61
00:04:11,876 --> 00:04:13,210
What a cute couple.

62
00:04:22,636 --> 00:04:24,388
Thanks. Goodnight.

63
00:04:24,472 --> 00:04:26,432
- Get home safely.
- Okay.

64
00:04:27,308 --> 00:04:29,059
- Wait.
- Get home safely.

65
00:04:29,143 --> 00:04:30,728
I'll sit in the front.

66
00:04:32,104 --> 00:04:34,565
- I'm going to sit in the front.
- Okay.

67
00:04:34,899 --> 00:04:39,737
I'm not saying this
because Tae-seop is my son.

68
00:04:39,820 --> 00:04:42,198
He's a good guy. Please give him a chance.

69
00:04:42,281 --> 00:04:43,449
Okay.

70
00:04:43,532 --> 00:04:48,204
And come to the restaurant anytime
if you have questions about our family.

71
00:04:48,287 --> 00:04:50,748
I'll tell you everything.
I won't hold anything back!

72
00:04:50,831 --> 00:04:52,291
- Thank you.
- Mom.

73
00:04:53,250 --> 00:04:54,251
Get in.

74
00:04:59,298 --> 00:05:00,508
Goodnight.

75
00:05:00,591 --> 00:05:01,884
Bye!

76
00:05:33,332 --> 00:05:35,000
Dating is different now.

77
00:05:35,793 --> 00:05:38,295
In our 20s,
it was just about us two being in love.

78
00:05:39,088 --> 00:05:41,924
But now, I can't just think
about how I feel.

79
00:05:43,300 --> 00:05:46,095
This might be my last relationship
before I get married.

80
00:05:47,513 --> 00:05:50,307
We have to consider
each other's families and finances.

81
00:05:50,683 --> 00:05:51,684
Oh, gosh!

82
00:05:52,059 --> 00:05:53,352
You scared me.

83
00:05:53,894 --> 00:05:54,937
Hey, Mom.

84
00:05:56,355 --> 00:05:58,816
Why are you so startled?

85
00:05:58,899 --> 00:06:00,693
I thought I'd walked into the wrong house.

86
00:06:01,026 --> 00:06:03,320
I was just thinking about something.

87
00:06:05,239 --> 00:06:06,615
You getting back from a workout?

88
00:06:06,699 --> 00:06:08,117
Yeah, I took a walk.

89
00:06:08,909 --> 00:06:09,910
And you?

90
00:06:10,452 --> 00:06:11,537
Me? You know...

91
00:06:12,705 --> 00:06:13,706
Mom.

92
00:06:14,039 --> 00:06:15,916
Out of curiosity,
let me ask you something.

93
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:19,211
What kind of man
would you want me to date?

94
00:06:19,295 --> 00:06:21,005
Am I the one dating him?

95
00:06:21,088 --> 00:06:23,841
Don't even bother if you can't be sure
without my approval.

96
00:06:23,924 --> 00:06:25,342
Get out of my way.

97
00:06:27,094 --> 00:06:29,388
Why did I even bother asking you?

98
00:06:29,471 --> 00:06:31,891
You never make anything easy for me.

99
00:06:31,974 --> 00:06:33,392
You're like a wicked stepmother.

100
00:06:35,853 --> 00:06:37,187
I call dibs on the shower!

101
00:06:45,988 --> 00:06:48,866
Yeah, it's my life and my love.

102
00:06:49,241 --> 00:06:51,160
I'll choose who I want
and deal with the consequences.

103
00:06:59,251 --> 00:07:00,336
Gosh.

104
00:07:06,216 --> 00:07:07,217
Hmm?

105
00:07:29,073 --> 00:07:30,574
I just got home.

106
00:07:30,783 --> 00:07:32,993
My mom made things awkward, didn't she?

107
00:07:33,410 --> 00:07:35,162
Don't let her get to you too much.

108
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:42,294
No, I had fun today.

109
00:07:43,003 --> 00:07:46,757
Tell your mom
it was really nice to meet her.

110
00:07:51,845 --> 00:07:54,223
I can never show my face
at her restaurant again.

111
00:07:56,976 --> 00:07:58,394
There goes one good restaurant.

112
00:08:30,467 --> 00:08:31,468
Wait.

113
00:08:32,011 --> 00:08:35,514
That's not what I should be worried about.
That's not the point!

114
00:08:38,142 --> 00:08:39,727
Honey, two orders of chicken feet.

115
00:08:39,810 --> 00:08:41,854
- One is extra spicy.
- Okay, honey.

116
00:09:03,667 --> 00:09:05,919
No, I can't do that! No way.

117
00:09:06,003 --> 00:09:07,421
I can only eat them.

118
00:09:07,629 --> 00:09:09,381
What do I do?

119
00:09:13,427 --> 00:09:14,428
Hey...

120
00:09:17,639 --> 00:09:18,849
Did you eat something spicy?

121
00:09:18,932 --> 00:09:21,852
Come on. It's lipstick!

122
00:09:23,353 --> 00:09:24,646
Why are you wearing lipstick?

123
00:09:25,564 --> 00:09:27,316
The weather's nice.

124
00:09:27,691 --> 00:09:30,027
The weather's warm, flowers are blooming

125
00:09:30,110 --> 00:09:31,320
and so is love.

126
00:09:31,403 --> 00:09:33,822
Who knows? An important guest might come.

127
00:09:34,198 --> 00:09:36,241
An important guest? Who?

128
00:09:36,325 --> 00:09:38,994
You remember

129
00:09:39,119 --> 00:09:42,081
that regular
who always closes the door so gently?

130
00:09:42,164 --> 00:09:45,918
Oh, the one you like
because she's so gentle with the door?

131
00:09:46,001 --> 00:09:47,836
Whose boyfriend always eats
chicken breast?

132
00:09:47,920 --> 00:09:49,213
Are you waiting for her?

133
00:09:49,296 --> 00:09:51,507
No, they aren't dating.

134
00:09:51,590 --> 00:09:54,009
That's all I can say for now.

135
00:09:54,218 --> 00:09:57,805
So, just...

136
00:09:58,764 --> 00:10:00,265
Forget it.

137
00:10:00,349 --> 00:10:02,851
You look perfect already.

138
00:10:03,727 --> 00:10:05,479
To make the chicken feet easier to eat...

139
00:10:05,562 --> 00:10:07,940
Hey, it's a show about your favorite food.

140
00:10:08,023 --> 00:10:09,775
My goodness.

141
00:10:10,567 --> 00:10:13,195
They go through three more boxes of those
per day.

142
00:10:14,321 --> 00:10:17,032
Man, every job is tough.

143
00:10:17,116 --> 00:10:18,408
My gosh.

144
00:10:19,034 --> 00:10:20,369
Oh...

145
00:10:20,452 --> 00:10:22,454
Let's watch something else.

146
00:10:23,497 --> 00:10:25,791
- I was watching that show!
- Son Jeong-a's scandals

147
00:10:25,874 --> 00:10:29,086
involving cheating and sexual bribes is
the talk of the town.

148
00:10:29,169 --> 00:10:31,046
But Son's agency

149
00:10:31,130 --> 00:10:33,048
hasn't made a public announcement

150
00:10:33,132 --> 00:10:35,801
to admit to or deny the allegations.

151
00:10:36,135 --> 00:10:38,011
- This scandal spread...
- Look at her face.

152
00:10:38,095 --> 00:10:39,304
in just a few days...

153
00:10:39,388 --> 00:10:41,390
Why would she do that
with a face like that?

154
00:10:41,473 --> 00:10:43,350
Right?

155
00:10:43,600 --> 00:10:45,102
The married movie director...

156
00:10:45,185 --> 00:10:47,354
- You can keep watching it.
- What?

157
00:10:47,437 --> 00:10:48,814
Rumor has it she's dating them.

158
00:10:48,897 --> 00:10:49,898
You're leaving?

159
00:10:49,982 --> 00:10:52,693
Yeah, my head hurts.
I need to get some exercise.

160
00:10:52,901 --> 00:10:53,902
Sure, then.

161
00:10:54,862 --> 00:10:56,822
- Someone in the industry...
- What's with her?

162
00:11:08,333 --> 00:11:10,627
How is he still sleeping?

163
00:11:12,880 --> 00:11:16,717
Are you the Sleeping Beauty?

164
00:11:17,259 --> 00:11:19,178
The Sleeping Prince?

165
00:11:25,684 --> 00:11:29,229
He's definitely more of a butler
than a prince.

166
00:11:31,648 --> 00:11:32,649
Oh?

167
00:11:35,194 --> 00:11:36,570
Hello, Deukgeun Deukgeun Gym.

168
00:11:36,653 --> 00:11:38,071
Or a laborer.

169
00:11:38,155 --> 00:11:40,949
You sound like you just woke up.
Are you home?

170
00:11:41,617 --> 00:11:43,035
Yeah, I am.

171
00:11:43,118 --> 00:11:46,038
Why? I'm all ready to go
to the gym right now.

172
00:11:46,121 --> 00:11:49,166
The gym's closed until the AC is fixed.

173
00:11:49,249 --> 00:11:51,543
Why don't you ever check
the announcement texts?

174
00:11:51,627 --> 00:11:55,214
Man, I was hoping
a workout would help my headache.

175
00:11:56,006 --> 00:11:57,799
Go out and take a walk.

176
00:11:57,883 --> 00:12:01,094
Engage your core and walk heel-to-toe.

177
00:12:01,178 --> 00:12:02,721
Walk 8,000 steps and send a photo

178
00:12:02,804 --> 00:12:04,514
- for proof.
- He's working in his sleep!

179
00:12:04,598 --> 00:12:06,808
Fine, then. Rest up.

180
00:12:07,184 --> 00:12:08,185
Okay.

181
00:12:10,979 --> 00:12:13,106
Alright, let's go on a walk.

182
00:12:13,565 --> 00:12:15,901
The heavier your legs get,
the lighter your heart gets.

183
00:12:17,861 --> 00:12:18,862
Huh?

184
00:12:21,531 --> 00:12:22,574
Hey!

185
00:12:25,535 --> 00:12:28,747
Aren't you going to wake up?
You haven't had a day off in forever!

186
00:12:29,456 --> 00:12:30,791
Don't you want to do anything?

187
00:12:32,292 --> 00:12:33,794
Go to the bank and the post office?

188
00:12:37,506 --> 00:12:38,507
Hmm?

189
00:12:39,508 --> 00:12:42,552
But it's the weekend.

190
00:12:43,553 --> 00:12:44,846
So, the laundromat?

191
00:12:49,810 --> 00:12:52,980
Not what you have to do!

192
00:12:53,063 --> 00:12:54,147
What do you want to do?

193
00:12:54,231 --> 00:12:57,401
How can you live
only doing things you have to do?

194
00:12:59,528 --> 00:13:03,073
Something cute and sweet
we can do together.

195
00:13:03,156 --> 00:13:04,366
Got anything?

196
00:13:05,575 --> 00:13:06,994
Oh, that?

197
00:13:07,786 --> 00:13:09,997
Of course!

198
00:13:10,080 --> 00:13:13,917
I want to travel somewhere warm.

199
00:13:14,126 --> 00:13:17,087
- Huh?
- But we can't teleport.

200
00:13:17,254 --> 00:13:18,297
We can't go.

201
00:13:18,380 --> 00:13:20,966
Are we really thinking about going abroad
all of a sudden?

202
00:13:21,967 --> 00:13:22,968
Hold up.

203
00:13:25,762 --> 00:13:27,472
We can't go

204
00:13:28,181 --> 00:13:30,642
but we could change

205
00:13:30,809 --> 00:13:33,270
the air around here.

206
00:13:36,523 --> 00:13:37,649
Let's make things humid

207
00:13:38,608 --> 00:13:40,861
and sticky.

208
00:13:44,489 --> 00:13:47,868
They're both actors.
Nothing weird about knowing each other.

209
00:13:49,536 --> 00:13:52,456
But the message sounded a bit...

210
00:13:53,165 --> 00:13:56,418
I have some important news for you.
Please meet me at The Hills.

211
00:13:56,918 --> 00:13:58,462
Man, I can't stop thinking about it.

212
00:14:04,509 --> 00:14:05,677
I came all the way here?

213
00:14:11,350 --> 00:14:12,351
Ui-yeong?

214
00:14:13,435 --> 00:14:14,436
Ui-yeong!

215
00:14:17,856 --> 00:14:18,857
Oh!

216
00:14:19,775 --> 00:14:20,776
Hey.

217
00:14:22,361 --> 00:14:24,446
Are you here to see me?

218
00:14:24,529 --> 00:14:27,657
Me? No, you saw me first.

219
00:14:27,741 --> 00:14:31,370
I'm just walking 8,000 steps
because my trainer told me to.

220
00:14:31,453 --> 00:14:34,498
Well, I'm glad you came.

221
00:14:34,998 --> 00:14:36,583
Come on in for some coffee.

222
00:15:01,066 --> 00:15:02,567
The marked one is decaf.

223
00:15:02,734 --> 00:15:03,860
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

224
00:15:03,944 --> 00:15:05,153
Enjoy.

225
00:15:13,203 --> 00:15:14,204
What?

226
00:15:15,539 --> 00:15:18,041
If you aren't pretending to read
just to spy on me

227
00:15:18,250 --> 00:15:19,584
why are you
still on the table of contents?

228
00:15:19,918 --> 00:15:21,837
You don't read, do you?

229
00:15:22,254 --> 00:15:26,508
You need to read the table of contents
to really understand a book.

230
00:15:26,591 --> 00:15:28,677
Sure, whatever.

231
00:15:32,139 --> 00:15:33,557
I'm off now.

232
00:15:33,849 --> 00:15:36,226
- How much do you have left?
- What?

233
00:15:36,351 --> 00:15:38,270
You have to walk 8,000 steps.

234
00:15:40,230 --> 00:15:41,606
I want some fresh air, too.

235
00:15:56,329 --> 00:15:57,372
Here.

236
00:16:04,171 --> 00:16:05,755
Why are we taking the stairs?

237
00:16:09,718 --> 00:16:10,802
The weather's perfect.

238
00:16:12,471 --> 00:16:15,557
But it might start raining anytime.
The weather's been crazy lately.

239
00:16:17,350 --> 00:16:19,060
Is something bothering you?

240
00:16:20,562 --> 00:16:21,605
You know.

241
00:16:22,189 --> 00:16:24,733
I always get a little blue
around this time of year.

242
00:16:26,443 --> 00:16:28,862
And you know
I usually ride my motorcycle everywhere.

243
00:16:29,321 --> 00:16:30,530
I should get some exercise.

244
00:16:31,072 --> 00:16:32,073
You?

245
00:16:32,449 --> 00:16:35,243
I'm sure you get thousands of steps in
just at the cafe.

246
00:16:35,494 --> 00:16:38,663
And acting takes a lot of energy, too.

247
00:16:38,747 --> 00:16:40,624
I may not get enough exercise, but you do.

248
00:16:41,958 --> 00:16:44,794
You think so?
I definitely need to exercise more, then.

249
00:16:46,338 --> 00:16:47,339
What?

250
00:16:59,267 --> 00:17:00,685
I quit my job at the theater.

251
00:17:01,561 --> 00:17:04,731
Really? But you performed
just a few days ago...

252
00:17:05,732 --> 00:17:06,858
Performed?

253
00:17:07,317 --> 00:17:11,905
I mean, you said you'd invite me
to your show soon.

254
00:17:12,572 --> 00:17:14,241
Oh, yeah, I did.

255
00:17:16,618 --> 00:17:18,161
Why? Are you disappointed?

256
00:17:18,453 --> 00:17:20,539
Should I put on a play just for you?

257
00:17:20,622 --> 00:17:23,833
Why would I ask you to do that?
That sounds like a proposal.

258
00:17:24,584 --> 00:17:26,753
Exactly. So, is that a yes?

259
00:17:33,301 --> 00:17:37,556
What are you going to do
about your acting career, then?

260
00:17:37,764 --> 00:17:40,475
No idea. If I never act again,
that's just life.

261
00:17:40,725 --> 00:17:42,561
I could shave my head
and join a monastery.

262
00:17:44,229 --> 00:17:45,647
Or maybe I'll also start dating.

263
00:17:49,651 --> 00:17:52,070
You were a handful for your parents,
weren't you?

264
00:17:52,571 --> 00:17:53,613
Was I?

265
00:17:55,824 --> 00:17:56,866
But it's okay.

266
00:17:58,451 --> 00:18:00,495
I don't have parents
to be a handful for anymore.

267
00:18:00,704 --> 00:18:03,582
You're the only one in the world
who's worried about me

268
00:18:03,832 --> 00:18:05,125
quitting acting.

269
00:18:10,005 --> 00:18:11,506
Getting 8,000 steps in is a lot!

270
00:18:13,925 --> 00:18:16,845
How many more steps do we have left?
We'd better hustle.

271
00:18:17,137 --> 00:18:18,138
Let's go.

272
00:18:25,270 --> 00:18:26,688
Jeong-a, open the door!

273
00:18:27,564 --> 00:18:28,607
Jeong-a!

274
00:18:30,692 --> 00:18:31,693
Come in.

275
00:18:38,742 --> 00:18:40,952
Why are you sweating?
Didn't you take a cab?

276
00:18:41,745 --> 00:18:43,038
It's a long hallway.

277
00:18:47,334 --> 00:18:49,878
We got a solid title

278
00:18:51,129 --> 00:18:53,840
and a bigger love story
to make people forget about the rumors.

279
00:18:54,507 --> 00:18:56,217
That was exactly what you wanted.

280
00:18:56,301 --> 00:18:57,385
Yeah.

281
00:18:57,802 --> 00:18:59,679
This reporter's a really good writer.

282
00:18:59,763 --> 00:19:01,598
I almost took that to a production agency.

283
00:19:02,015 --> 00:19:04,267
So, why don't you want it published?

284
00:19:04,351 --> 00:19:05,810
Dr. Shin also wants it out soon.

285
00:19:05,894 --> 00:19:08,563
Everyone's just waiting for your approval.

286
00:19:09,064 --> 00:19:12,150
I like it, but someone else doesn't.

287
00:19:13,026 --> 00:19:15,945
He's begging me to leave him out,
so what can I do?

288
00:19:16,029 --> 00:19:17,155
What about you?

289
00:19:17,947 --> 00:19:19,366
Are you going to retire for good?

290
00:19:20,659 --> 00:19:23,703
I'll just lay low until things blow over.

291
00:19:23,787 --> 00:19:26,831
People will forget about me
as soon as some new gossip surfaces.

292
00:19:26,915 --> 00:19:28,041
My gosh.

293
00:19:28,416 --> 00:19:31,920
You frustrate me and make me feel better
at the same time.

294
00:19:35,256 --> 00:19:38,802
Anyway, I need to take care of something
while I'm staying low.

295
00:19:38,927 --> 00:19:40,261
It's about Ms. Lee Yun-jeong.

296
00:19:40,929 --> 00:19:44,516
Can you check if she also got
her surgery done at Dr. Shin's hospital?

297
00:19:45,225 --> 00:19:46,976
Good afternoon

298
00:19:47,185 --> 00:19:49,104
ladies and gentlemen.

299
00:19:49,312 --> 00:19:52,691
This is Captain Jung speaking.

300
00:19:53,566 --> 00:19:56,444
Hyun-min! I got everything you told me to.

301
00:19:57,237 --> 00:20:00,532
Welcome aboard to Hyun-min Airlines.

302
00:20:18,049 --> 00:20:19,968
I can't wear this!

303
00:20:20,093 --> 00:20:21,845
- But it looks great.
- Really?

304
00:20:24,973 --> 00:20:25,974
Please!

305
00:20:29,352 --> 00:20:31,354
Desert island! Come on!

306
00:20:31,604 --> 00:20:33,314
One, two, three, four.

307
00:20:33,398 --> 00:20:35,483
Yes, Singapore!

308
00:20:38,695 --> 00:20:40,029
Cheers!

309
00:20:40,864 --> 00:20:42,574
- Open up!
- Open up!

310
00:20:58,381 --> 00:20:59,591
You know

311
00:21:00,592 --> 00:21:03,428
I didn't expect this last-minute getaway
to be so great.

312
00:21:03,511 --> 00:21:06,014
I'm watching a fake sunset at a fake beach

313
00:21:06,848 --> 00:21:07,849
so why am I so happy?

314
00:21:07,932 --> 00:21:09,476
Why else?

315
00:21:09,559 --> 00:21:11,019
Because I'm with you.

316
00:21:11,478 --> 00:21:14,189
It's stupid if you do it alone

317
00:21:14,272 --> 00:21:16,733
but romantic when you do it with someone.

318
00:21:17,150 --> 00:21:18,485
Some things are just like that.

319
00:21:21,362 --> 00:21:23,072
So romantic.

320
00:21:23,948 --> 00:21:25,158
It's so romantic!

321
00:21:26,910 --> 00:21:27,911
Very romantic.

322
00:21:29,287 --> 00:21:31,998
I haven't enjoyed romance in so long.
Glad to have it back.

323
00:21:33,875 --> 00:21:37,295
But I still need to go
to the laundromat tomorrow.

324
00:21:38,046 --> 00:21:39,756
I can't wash my sheets at home.

325
00:21:42,759 --> 00:21:44,719
You can't live only doing what you love.

326
00:21:44,803 --> 00:21:46,596
You have to do what needs to be done, too.

327
00:21:47,472 --> 00:21:50,391
But I'll wash the sheets tomorrow.

328
00:21:51,893 --> 00:21:53,061
- Tomorrow?
- Yeah.

329
00:22:03,321 --> 00:22:05,824
THE DEERFIDDICH POP-UP EVENT IS NOW OVER.
THANK YOU FOR YOUR INTEREST

330
00:22:36,271 --> 00:22:37,272
Hey.

331
00:22:37,939 --> 00:22:40,275
It's nothing big.

332
00:22:40,692 --> 00:22:43,152
You've done great work.

333
00:22:43,236 --> 00:22:44,654
I know it.

334
00:22:45,738 --> 00:22:47,824
But we can't offer you
a permanent contract.

335
00:22:48,157 --> 00:22:50,577
Every mistake stands out
when you're an intern

336
00:22:50,660 --> 00:22:52,328
because interns don't get much time.

337
00:22:52,412 --> 00:22:55,081
That's just how things work.

338
00:22:55,248 --> 00:22:58,877
It's a part of your role here
to accept the result, too.

339
00:23:00,211 --> 00:23:01,212
Yes, sir.

340
00:23:01,337 --> 00:23:03,965
I hate that I have to tell you this.

341
00:23:04,048 --> 00:23:06,301
Can you imagine how terrible I feel?

342
00:23:06,843 --> 00:23:08,636
I'm sorry.

343
00:23:08,720 --> 00:23:10,305
No, don't be.

344
00:23:11,431 --> 00:23:14,058
Alright, then.

345
00:23:14,183 --> 00:23:17,478
But it's not like you're leaving
right away.

346
00:23:21,274 --> 00:23:23,568
Hey, Mr. An!

347
00:23:23,651 --> 00:23:25,361
Hey, how have you been?

348
00:23:25,486 --> 00:23:26,946
The same, of course.

349
00:23:28,156 --> 00:23:29,490
I heard

350
00:23:29,616 --> 00:23:31,492
Mr. Kang was leaving Legal.

351
00:23:31,826 --> 00:23:34,203
That's too bad. He was a great guy.

352
00:23:34,287 --> 00:23:36,039
He's joining a law firm.

353
00:23:36,122 --> 00:23:38,625
He kept joking about returning
if things got too hard

354
00:23:38,708 --> 00:23:40,376
so I told him we don't hire traitors.

355
00:23:40,460 --> 00:23:42,128
I said we could grab drinks instead.

356
00:23:42,211 --> 00:23:43,713
Yeah, he wanted more money, huh?

357
00:23:43,963 --> 00:23:45,590
You got time for coffee?

358
00:23:45,840 --> 00:23:47,091
Sure.

359
00:23:47,175 --> 00:23:49,052
I haven't seen you in so long.

360
00:23:49,302 --> 00:23:50,553
We should get drinks.

361
00:23:54,349 --> 00:23:55,808
CLOSED OVER THE WEEKEND
TO FIX THE AIR CONDITIONERS

362
00:23:58,102 --> 00:24:00,104
This wind was worth paying for!

363
00:24:02,315 --> 00:24:03,691
Did you go somewhere nice?

364
00:24:04,275 --> 00:24:05,652
You're glowing.

365
00:24:07,695 --> 00:24:09,656
No need to go anywhere to enjoy a holiday.

366
00:24:09,739 --> 00:24:12,492
It's a vacation as long as you're relaxed.

367
00:24:12,742 --> 00:24:15,870
Don't forget to extend the passes
for all our clients today.

368
00:24:15,954 --> 00:24:16,955
Okay.

369
00:24:24,837 --> 00:24:25,880
Are you at work now?

370
00:24:25,964 --> 00:24:28,633
I'm still a bit groggy from the jetlag.

371
00:24:29,801 --> 00:24:30,802
Just kidding.

372
00:24:31,052 --> 00:24:32,261
Have a great day.

373
00:24:33,471 --> 00:24:34,597
He's so tacky.

374
00:24:36,015 --> 00:24:38,851
Hyun-min, they're taking down
the pop-up set now, right?

375
00:24:39,227 --> 00:24:43,189
Yeah, Marketing is getting the things
to send back to the brand.

376
00:24:44,899 --> 00:24:47,068
And the HOME employees should be here
anytime soon.

377
00:24:48,069 --> 00:24:49,070
- Oh?
- Oh?

378
00:24:49,153 --> 00:24:50,405
NEW MAIL:
SIM SAE-BYEOK'S INTERNSHIP TERMINATION

379
00:24:54,784 --> 00:24:56,494
MS. SIM SAE-BYEOK'S INTERNSHIP
WILL BE TERMINATED ON AUGUST 7, 2025

380
00:24:56,577 --> 00:24:58,079
WE'D LIKE TO THANK MS. SIM
FOR HER HARD WORK AND WISH HER THE BEST

381
00:25:01,374 --> 00:25:04,043
Now that I think about it,
she's been gone for a while.

382
00:25:05,044 --> 00:25:06,713
Maybe she already heard the news.

383
00:25:08,756 --> 00:25:10,258
Let's give her some time.

384
00:25:10,758 --> 00:25:13,052
She'll need some space
to process it on her own.

385
00:25:15,471 --> 00:25:16,472
Okay.

386
00:25:38,786 --> 00:25:40,913
It's a perfect day to tear the set down.

387
00:25:42,957 --> 00:25:43,958
Hello.

388
00:25:44,250 --> 00:25:45,501
- Hi!
- Hello.

389
00:25:45,585 --> 00:25:46,586
Hello.

390
00:25:48,421 --> 00:25:49,881
It's been a minute.

391
00:25:49,964 --> 00:25:52,717
Yeah, it's been a minute.

392
00:25:54,969 --> 00:25:56,512
Should we get started?

393
00:25:56,888 --> 00:25:59,223
- Yes, sir.
- Let's go.

394
00:25:59,307 --> 00:26:00,475
Be safe!

395
00:26:00,558 --> 00:26:01,559
See you later.

396
00:26:16,240 --> 00:26:17,366
Can you take that out?

397
00:26:17,450 --> 00:26:18,826
One, two, three.

398
00:26:27,752 --> 00:26:29,003
I think that should be good.

399
00:26:33,216 --> 00:26:34,217
Ui-yeong?

400
00:26:35,593 --> 00:26:36,594
Oh, sorry.

401
00:26:37,470 --> 00:26:39,472
It's the order list for the tray tables.

402
00:26:39,555 --> 00:26:40,890
I've e-mailed it to you, too.

403
00:26:40,973 --> 00:26:42,600
It should make things easier for you.

404
00:26:42,683 --> 00:26:43,726
Thanks.

405
00:26:43,810 --> 00:26:46,187
Is something wrong?

406
00:26:46,270 --> 00:26:47,313
Oh, well...

407
00:26:48,147 --> 00:26:52,026
Our intern's contract has been terminated.

408
00:26:52,485 --> 00:26:54,779
I'm just worried about her.

409
00:26:55,154 --> 00:26:58,574
Really? I thought she was great.
She worked hard.

410
00:26:58,658 --> 00:27:00,910
Yeah, she's so kind and passionate

411
00:27:00,993 --> 00:27:03,871
but she became so timid
after making one mistake.

412
00:27:17,343 --> 00:27:19,554
- Ms. Sae-byeok.
- Yes?

413
00:27:23,724 --> 00:27:27,311
Don't just use your wrists or hands
when using a tool.

414
00:27:27,395 --> 00:27:28,813
Put your weight into it.

415
00:27:28,896 --> 00:27:30,982
- I see.
- This should work.

416
00:27:32,525 --> 00:27:35,987
You want me to use this?

417
00:27:37,905 --> 00:27:39,407
One more tip.

418
00:27:39,490 --> 00:27:42,285
It's even better
if you put some feeling into it.

419
00:27:42,493 --> 00:27:45,288
Picture the faces of the colleagues
who gave you a hard time.

420
00:27:46,038 --> 00:27:47,039
Okay.

421
00:28:00,011 --> 00:28:01,804
Sae-byeok would've taken me seriously

422
00:28:03,347 --> 00:28:05,808
if it weren't for you.

423
00:28:11,189 --> 00:28:14,150
We're just asking one more company
so you have more work.

424
00:28:14,233 --> 00:28:15,860
Let's keep things simple.

425
00:28:20,698 --> 00:28:23,576
I hate that I have to tell you this.

426
00:28:23,659 --> 00:28:25,745
Can you imagine how terrible I feel?

427
00:28:33,502 --> 00:28:36,464
I feel like a giant speck of dust.

428
00:28:36,547 --> 00:28:39,091
We've been here for years.
Why are we still doing demolition?

429
00:28:39,175 --> 00:28:40,968
Even our bosses are doing it.

430
00:28:42,303 --> 00:28:44,472
I wish we had a newbie
so that we'd have less work.

431
00:28:45,014 --> 00:28:46,432
- Right?
- Yeah.

432
00:28:46,515 --> 00:28:47,516
That's scary.

433
00:28:47,600 --> 00:28:50,728
Even 70-year-olds are the young ones
doing chores in nursing homes.

434
00:28:51,562 --> 00:28:53,898
Who's been hammering that hard all day?

435
00:29:07,912 --> 00:29:09,747
Should we order dinner?

436
00:29:11,207 --> 00:29:13,376
I'm worried I'll get drowsy if I eat now.

437
00:29:14,210 --> 00:29:15,461
Okay, then.

438
00:29:18,256 --> 00:29:19,840
- Have this first.
- Hmm?

439
00:29:19,924 --> 00:29:21,634
It's the perfect pick-me-up.

440
00:29:21,717 --> 00:29:23,052
Keep it and eat it as needed.

441
00:29:23,135 --> 00:29:24,387
Nice, thank you.

442
00:29:26,222 --> 00:29:28,391
Go hit the sauna and grab some dinner.

443
00:29:28,474 --> 00:29:30,268
I'll stay here and check the orders.

444
00:29:30,351 --> 00:29:32,603
- Oh, and on your way back...
- Yeah, anything, right?

445
00:29:33,312 --> 00:29:34,355
Yeah.

446
00:29:37,191 --> 00:29:39,527
We'll shower and meet at the lobby
in 30 minutes, okay?

447
00:29:39,777 --> 00:29:42,113
- You'd better not fall asleep again.
- I might.

448
00:29:42,196 --> 00:29:44,532
Cheer up! Don't skip your meals!

449
00:29:44,907 --> 00:29:47,910
Wait! Don't just get me anything
on your way back.

450
00:29:48,369 --> 00:29:49,495
Get me something good.

451
00:29:50,705 --> 00:29:52,957
Sure, we'll do that.

452
00:29:53,040 --> 00:29:54,375
Okay, something good.

453
00:29:54,458 --> 00:29:55,793
What does he like?

454
00:29:55,918 --> 00:29:57,211
I don't know, something tasty.

455
00:29:57,295 --> 00:29:59,005
What's tasty?

456
00:30:12,852 --> 00:30:13,853
This is good.

457
00:30:18,733 --> 00:30:21,610
Stop acting
like an arrogant and childish bastard.

458
00:30:21,694 --> 00:30:23,279
This underground shelter you seek is

459
00:30:23,362 --> 00:30:25,281
the most desperate stage for us!

460
00:30:39,295 --> 00:30:42,298
AN EXCLUSIVE INSIGHT
INTO SON JEONG-A'S LOVE STORY!

461
00:30:45,134 --> 00:30:47,219
SHE'S ALREADY REGISTERED HER MARRIAGE
WITH A PROFESSOR FROM A BIG HOSPITAL

462
00:31:03,903 --> 00:31:05,654
When did you start sponsoring the troupe?

463
00:31:05,738 --> 00:31:07,573
How did you know I was in it?

464
00:31:07,656 --> 00:31:09,116
I was doing fine on my own!

465
00:31:09,992 --> 00:31:11,786
Why did you make me look so helpless?

466
00:31:11,869 --> 00:31:13,496
Come in. Let's talk inside.

467
00:31:29,053 --> 00:31:30,679
THE MODEL IN QUESTION TURNS OUT
TO BE HER STEPSON

468
00:31:34,517 --> 00:31:35,601
Read the article.

469
00:31:35,684 --> 00:31:39,313
Only Ms. Son's closest people
will go to her suite for the next bit.

470
00:31:39,397 --> 00:31:41,232
AN EXCLUSIVE INSIGHT
INTO SON JEONG-A'S LOVE STORY!

471
00:31:44,735 --> 00:31:47,196
THE ALLEGATIONS OF BRIBES AND THE AFFAIR
ARE ALSO FALSE

472
00:31:51,700 --> 00:31:52,701
Huh?

473
00:31:58,707 --> 00:32:00,793
SON JEONG-A

474
00:32:00,876 --> 00:32:03,963
SON JEONG-AH, ACTRESS

475
00:32:11,554 --> 00:32:13,264
There are so many articles.

476
00:32:16,851 --> 00:32:19,937
How is Ji-su her stepson?

477
00:32:23,274 --> 00:32:24,733
But Ji-su said...

478
00:32:25,568 --> 00:32:28,362
he didn't have parents
who'd worry about him.

479
00:32:34,201 --> 00:32:36,287
How did she manage to hide
her marriage for years?

480
00:32:36,370 --> 00:32:39,790
He got remarried
after his first wife passed.

481
00:32:39,874 --> 00:32:41,459
I'm sure they wanted to be careful.

482
00:32:41,959 --> 00:32:43,544
The bigger your family becomes

483
00:32:43,627 --> 00:32:45,546
the more you keep your mouth shut.
Look at me.

484
00:32:47,423 --> 00:32:48,591
But is it true?

485
00:32:48,674 --> 00:32:51,969
That the stepson is the guy
who works at the cafe we always go to?

486
00:32:52,094 --> 00:32:54,305
They've released
pretty much all info on him.

487
00:32:54,388 --> 00:32:56,599
It's not like he did anything bad.

488
00:32:56,682 --> 00:33:00,895
Everyone's just jealous
his parents are a doctor and an actress.

489
00:33:00,978 --> 00:33:04,148
I know! I knew there was
something about him from the start.

490
00:33:13,282 --> 00:33:14,783
ARE YOU OKAY? YOU'RE ON TV.
WHAT'S GOING ON?

491
00:33:14,867 --> 00:33:16,243
HELLO, I'M PRODUCER PARK.
PLEASE CALL ME WHEN YOU CAN

492
00:33:16,327 --> 00:33:17,786
HEY, THAT'S YOU, RIGHT?
IS THAT REALLY YOU ON THE NEWS?

493
00:33:18,287 --> 00:33:19,997
Seriously, of all days...

494
00:33:23,375 --> 00:33:24,418
SLIDE TO POWER OFF

495
00:33:27,713 --> 00:33:29,089
Is this where the stepson works?

496
00:33:29,173 --> 00:33:30,216
- Wait.
- Let's check.

497
00:33:30,299 --> 00:33:32,176
- Are you sure?
- Yeah, this is it.

498
00:33:32,259 --> 00:33:34,136
- Are you sure?
- Maybe he knows we're here.

499
00:33:34,220 --> 00:33:35,930
- Maybe he ran away.
- When is he coming?

500
00:33:36,013 --> 00:33:37,181
Damn it.

501
00:33:42,186 --> 00:33:44,438
The caller is unavailable.

502
00:33:44,522 --> 00:33:47,066
You will be directed to voicemail.

503
00:33:47,816 --> 00:33:49,485
Why is his phone off?

504
00:33:53,864 --> 00:33:54,990
Where are you?

505
00:33:55,241 --> 00:33:57,201
Call me when you see my message.

506
00:33:59,578 --> 00:34:05,751
WHERE YOUR FUN TRIP BEGINS

507
00:34:25,688 --> 00:34:26,855
Ui-yeong.

508
00:34:27,982 --> 00:34:32,361
It's Sae-byeok's last day today.
Should we grab a drink after?

509
00:34:33,112 --> 00:34:36,782
Sorry, I have plans tonight.

510
00:34:36,865 --> 00:34:40,411
Let's have a farewell party next time.
I have to go. Bye.

511
00:34:41,412 --> 00:34:42,413
Ui-yeong!

512
00:34:43,038 --> 00:34:44,039
See you.

513
00:34:49,878 --> 00:34:52,131
- Hello, sir.
- Hey, Ui-yeong.

514
00:34:52,214 --> 00:34:54,341
Did Ji-su show up for work?

515
00:35:04,810 --> 00:35:07,021
MEORU ART CENTER

516
00:35:07,187 --> 00:35:10,149
I'm more than happy to get the treatment

517
00:35:10,232 --> 00:35:12,651
but Dr. Lee doesn't think
it's a good idea!

518
00:35:13,152 --> 00:35:17,072
You're 60. What treatment?

519
00:35:17,156 --> 00:35:19,867
Sure, I'm 60, but I still want to live!

520
00:35:21,452 --> 00:35:22,494
Sorry.

521
00:35:23,203 --> 00:35:25,164
What brings you here?

522
00:35:25,247 --> 00:35:27,124
Oh, hello.

523
00:35:27,207 --> 00:35:29,084
I'm Ji-su's friend.

524
00:35:33,130 --> 00:35:34,465
He's not here.

525
00:35:35,215 --> 00:35:36,425
He quit.

526
00:35:36,508 --> 00:35:38,218
Yeah, I know that.

527
00:35:38,677 --> 00:35:40,888
But do you know his home address

528
00:35:40,971 --> 00:35:45,059
or where he goes often,
a restaurant or something?

529
00:35:45,184 --> 00:35:48,062
Ji-su disappeared.

530
00:35:48,145 --> 00:35:50,648
He didn't come to work at the cafe,
and I can't reach him.

531
00:35:51,982 --> 00:35:54,443
Maybe he just got fed up
and needed some space.

532
00:35:54,526 --> 00:35:57,029
I know his address,
so check there first...

533
00:35:57,112 --> 00:35:58,989
Hold on. What day is it today?

534
00:35:59,365 --> 00:36:01,033
It's the 7th.

535
00:36:05,162 --> 00:36:06,163
He didn't disappear.

536
00:36:15,756 --> 00:36:20,135
LEE YUN-JEONG

537
00:36:25,140 --> 00:36:26,141
Mom.

538
00:36:30,396 --> 00:36:32,189
Mom, your baby's here.

539
00:36:35,275 --> 00:36:38,570
I said I'd visit more, but here I am,
only showing up for your memorial again.

540
00:36:41,949 --> 00:36:44,785
I've just been busy with work.
I didn't forget about you.

541
00:36:46,328 --> 00:36:50,165
Look. I even brought a bunch of coffee,
your favorite.

542
00:36:58,674 --> 00:37:00,134
I didn't even let you

543
00:37:02,136 --> 00:37:04,346
drink any coffee after the surgery.

544
00:37:09,143 --> 00:37:10,310
I regret that.

545
00:37:11,854 --> 00:37:14,606
I should've let you have coffee
when you said you felt sluggish.

546
00:37:15,107 --> 00:37:17,317
That could've helped you recover.

547
00:37:21,196 --> 00:37:22,322
You know

548
00:37:24,950 --> 00:37:27,035
these days,
I just want to get a coffee with you.

549
00:37:30,164 --> 00:37:32,666
I want to sit at a sunny cafe with you

550
00:37:33,250 --> 00:37:34,752
and talk about life...

551
00:37:37,379 --> 00:37:38,839
and people.

552
00:37:45,345 --> 00:37:47,639
They won't be able to function
if I quit the troupe.

553
00:37:47,723 --> 00:37:49,516
Who's going to do the errands and clean?

554
00:37:49,600 --> 00:37:51,226
And everyone looks like a potato.

555
00:37:56,356 --> 00:37:58,776
Mom, try the coffee. I made it.

556
00:38:53,121 --> 00:38:55,666
What? How did you know I'd be here?

557
00:38:56,875 --> 00:38:58,919
I told you the weather's been crazy.

558
00:39:00,587 --> 00:39:02,214
I knew you wouldn't have an umbrella.

559
00:39:03,215 --> 00:39:06,260
How did you know
it was my mom's memorial day?

560
00:39:11,932 --> 00:39:12,975
Hold this for a sec.

561
00:39:19,857 --> 00:39:21,692
LEE YUN-JEONG

562
00:39:44,464 --> 00:39:45,507
What were you thinking?

563
00:39:46,216 --> 00:39:48,427
What's my mom going to think of us?

564
00:39:49,803 --> 00:39:51,305
You sure you can explain it to her?

565
00:39:51,722 --> 00:39:53,307
She's really old-fashioned, you know.

566
00:39:57,185 --> 00:40:00,480
She'll just think
I'm a dear friend who looks out for you.

567
00:40:01,231 --> 00:40:03,525
Are you that worried about me?

568
00:40:05,569 --> 00:40:07,863
You took me to the hospital

569
00:40:08,113 --> 00:40:09,907
and gave me a ride on your bike, too.

570
00:40:11,366 --> 00:40:13,285
You found me at my weakest.

571
00:40:14,036 --> 00:40:15,495
I don't know how to accept this.

572
00:40:19,625 --> 00:40:20,709
And...

573
00:40:23,128 --> 00:40:24,922
I wasn't the only one worried about you.

574
00:40:26,840 --> 00:40:29,384
Why did they have to publish this
on his mom's memorial day?

575
00:40:29,468 --> 00:40:30,719
Man.

576
00:40:30,886 --> 00:40:33,263
I bet he's having a breakdown somewhere.

577
00:40:33,347 --> 00:40:34,640
Who wrote this?

578
00:40:34,723 --> 00:40:37,184
- Report the reporter.
- I found it!

579
00:40:37,851 --> 00:40:39,061
The Haneulbal Memorial Park!

580
00:40:40,062 --> 00:40:42,189
Oh, yeah, I went with him last year.

581
00:40:42,856 --> 00:40:45,108
Shouldn't we go and check on him?

582
00:40:45,192 --> 00:40:48,779
He may have quit,
but we're his only lifelong friends.

583
00:40:48,862 --> 00:40:50,656
We should at least sit and drink with him.

584
00:40:51,281 --> 00:40:53,575
Let's go. Today's rehearsal is canceled.

585
00:40:53,909 --> 00:40:57,663
No, I'll go instead.

586
00:41:05,712 --> 00:41:06,713
Let's see.

587
00:41:08,966 --> 00:41:12,886
Ui-yeong, we got the wood for the tables,
so I'll cut them before I go today.

588
00:41:13,178 --> 00:41:14,972
What are you doing? Are you off work?

589
00:41:18,392 --> 00:41:20,102
Hey! It's raining.

590
00:41:20,185 --> 00:41:21,728
Did you bring all the wood inside?

591
00:41:21,812 --> 00:41:24,022
Oh, it's still in the truck.

592
00:41:24,356 --> 00:41:26,733
Didn't you check the weather?

593
00:41:27,067 --> 00:41:28,360
Get your act together!

594
00:41:29,069 --> 00:41:30,112
Damn it!

595
00:41:32,531 --> 00:41:34,533
Cover them right now! Hurry!

596
00:41:35,117 --> 00:41:36,159
Here!

597
00:41:36,660 --> 00:41:38,370
Move faster!

598
00:41:38,453 --> 00:41:39,746
Come on! Hurry!

599
00:41:41,456 --> 00:41:42,457
Okay!

600
00:41:45,502 --> 00:41:47,337
- Jin-su!
- Jin-su!

601
00:41:47,504 --> 00:41:48,588
- Jin-su!
- Jin-su!

602
00:41:50,090 --> 00:41:51,383
Call 9-1-1 right now!

603
00:41:53,218 --> 00:41:55,095
Oh, no.

604
00:41:56,013 --> 00:41:57,014
Jin-su!

605
00:41:57,180 --> 00:41:58,390
Is this 9-1-1?

606
00:41:59,516 --> 00:42:01,309
Why are you still at the office?

607
00:42:02,310 --> 00:42:05,147
He could've broken his spine from the fall

608
00:42:05,230 --> 00:42:08,316
but he only fractured his arm.
The doctor says that's a huge relief.

609
00:42:09,067 --> 00:42:10,986
You don't need to come down here.

610
00:42:11,111 --> 00:42:12,404
He's out.

611
00:42:14,573 --> 00:42:15,574
How are you?

612
00:42:15,657 --> 00:42:18,618
Sorry, I know you always told me
to be careful.

613
00:42:18,702 --> 00:42:20,746
No need to be sorry. We're sorry.

614
00:42:20,829 --> 00:42:22,539
We need to re-order the wood, right?

615
00:42:23,123 --> 00:42:24,374
We're already shorthanded.

616
00:42:24,458 --> 00:42:25,709
Are you the CEO?

617
00:42:25,792 --> 00:42:27,461
Don't worry about that.

618
00:42:28,045 --> 00:42:29,963
I'll take care of it.

619
00:42:30,047 --> 00:42:31,506
Just focus on getting better.

620
00:42:31,590 --> 00:42:34,509
And nothing matters more than safety.

621
00:42:34,968 --> 00:42:36,553
- Remember that.
- Okay.

622
00:42:36,762 --> 00:42:38,638
Hey, did it hurt a lot?

623
00:42:38,722 --> 00:42:40,182
Man.

624
00:42:40,682 --> 00:42:43,060
You're still so handsome,
even with a scar on your face.

625
00:42:49,232 --> 00:42:51,526
Jeong-a is such a legend.

626
00:42:51,610 --> 00:42:54,321
I know, right?
I couldn't have done that if I were her.

627
00:42:54,404 --> 00:42:56,823
I know. I love her more now.

628
00:42:57,616 --> 00:42:58,658
She's amazing!

629
00:42:58,950 --> 00:43:00,452
Seriously, she's so cool.

630
00:43:06,750 --> 00:43:07,751
Ji-su.

631
00:43:09,127 --> 00:43:10,837
I knew you were the model

632
00:43:12,005 --> 00:43:13,507
in that rumor.

633
00:43:14,007 --> 00:43:15,050
What?

634
00:43:17,344 --> 00:43:19,054
Whatever it is

635
00:43:19,387 --> 00:43:21,640
don't try so hard to run from it.

636
00:43:22,849 --> 00:43:25,060
Use that time and effort

637
00:43:26,603 --> 00:43:28,939
to stand for what you love.

638
00:43:29,523 --> 00:43:31,316
I'm sure there are things you love.

639
00:43:32,526 --> 00:43:35,529
Do that for a day, a month, then a year.

640
00:43:36,863 --> 00:43:38,490
Keep it up

641
00:43:39,199 --> 00:43:43,161
and one day, you'll feel just fine.

642
00:43:51,670 --> 00:43:52,921
Thank you.

643
00:43:59,553 --> 00:44:01,263
Keep your phone on.

644
00:44:01,721 --> 00:44:02,722
Okay.

645
00:44:03,348 --> 00:44:04,766
Thanks for today.

646
00:44:05,851 --> 00:44:09,521
And let me know anytime
if you need my help.

647
00:44:10,438 --> 00:44:11,439
I will.

648
00:44:18,572 --> 00:44:22,534
Those who overcome hardships
become invincible.

649
00:44:23,034 --> 00:44:27,164
Dr. Shin was the strongest candidate
before the rumors, anyway.

650
00:44:27,539 --> 00:44:30,500
But we can't just decide it like this.

651
00:44:30,584 --> 00:44:32,460
I know you're especially disappointed

652
00:44:32,544 --> 00:44:35,255
but everything's in Dr. Shin's favor.

653
00:44:35,589 --> 00:44:39,718
The VIPs are already lined up
for an appointment with him.

654
00:44:42,929 --> 00:44:44,723
Sorry, my meetings ran late.

655
00:44:45,182 --> 00:44:46,766
I guess you're already talking.

656
00:44:46,850 --> 00:44:49,895
Here comes
our hospital's biggest romantic!

657
00:44:50,061 --> 00:44:51,062
Have a seat.

658
00:44:59,571 --> 00:45:02,449
Sir, please think about it one more time.

659
00:45:02,532 --> 00:45:04,492
You should take more time
to think about it.

660
00:45:04,576 --> 00:45:06,912
- See you tomorrow.
- But you have to think

661
00:45:07,162 --> 00:45:09,623
about the hospital's reputation.

662
00:45:21,593 --> 00:45:27,140
SON JEONG-A

663
00:45:31,353 --> 00:45:36,024
REPORTER YOON FROM SPOTLIGHT

664
00:45:40,278 --> 00:45:41,696
Hi, it's Shin Ji-hun.

665
00:45:42,781 --> 00:45:44,115
Thanks for the article.

666
00:45:45,617 --> 00:45:46,660
Well

667
00:45:47,202 --> 00:45:50,330
it seems like my friends and colleagues
loved it even more.

668
00:46:06,263 --> 00:46:07,973
Do you need anything?

669
00:46:08,056 --> 00:46:09,724
Oh, it's nothing.

670
00:46:10,809 --> 00:46:13,770
Mr. Lim, you remember the woman

671
00:46:14,062 --> 00:46:16,606
who brought that big cooler last time?

672
00:46:16,690 --> 00:46:18,108
- Yeah.
- Does she work out here?

673
00:46:18,233 --> 00:46:19,442
No, she's my girl...

674
00:46:21,361 --> 00:46:22,946
Why do you ask?

675
00:46:23,029 --> 00:46:25,156
I thought she looked familiar.

676
00:46:25,490 --> 00:46:27,033
I was wondering where I saw her

677
00:46:28,159 --> 00:46:29,286
but I remembered

678
00:46:29,661 --> 00:46:31,288
that I met her on a dating app.

679
00:46:31,371 --> 00:46:33,581
We're basically meant to be, huh?

680
00:46:34,040 --> 00:46:36,334
I'm sure it's not her.

681
00:46:36,418 --> 00:46:39,754
No, I remember her big feet.

682
00:46:39,838 --> 00:46:42,173
Her feet? How do you know that?

683
00:46:42,257 --> 00:46:43,883
And well

684
00:46:44,426 --> 00:46:46,886
she said she loved my sexy forearms.

685
00:46:47,095 --> 00:46:49,931
It's hard to forget such a compliment.

686
00:46:51,057 --> 00:46:52,976
I can't wear this!

687
00:46:53,059 --> 00:46:54,811
- But it looks great.
- Really?

688
00:46:55,103 --> 00:46:57,731
I really want to see her again.

689
00:46:57,814 --> 00:46:59,316
Does she not have a membership?

690
00:46:59,941 --> 00:47:01,484
No, she doesn't.

691
00:47:01,609 --> 00:47:02,902
- Okay, then.
- Yeah.

692
00:47:09,075 --> 00:47:10,410
- Come again!
- Thank you.

693
00:47:10,493 --> 00:47:11,619
Bye.

694
00:47:13,121 --> 00:47:14,831
Sorry about not coming to work.

695
00:47:15,957 --> 00:47:18,251
The news got out on my mom's memorial day.

696
00:47:18,793 --> 00:47:20,211
I saw the reporters and panicked.

697
00:47:20,295 --> 00:47:23,673
I didn't know
you were going through all that.

698
00:47:23,840 --> 00:47:25,633
So, is everything sorted now?

699
00:47:26,009 --> 00:47:29,137
No, nothing's settled yet

700
00:47:30,013 --> 00:47:31,056
but I need to work.

701
00:47:31,473 --> 00:47:33,933
I know I have a lot of nerve,
but please give me a chance.

702
00:47:34,017 --> 00:47:35,518
I'll work really hard.

703
00:47:35,810 --> 00:47:38,229
Promise me you'll call me
before you skip work next time.

704
00:47:40,815 --> 00:47:41,858
Thank you.

705
00:47:55,372 --> 00:47:56,414
I'll take that.

706
00:47:57,165 --> 00:47:59,125
- I can take it.
- Thank you.

707
00:48:08,301 --> 00:48:09,469
Wait.

708
00:48:12,222 --> 00:48:14,140
Why hasn't Ui-yeong come in
for coffee yet?

709
00:48:15,266 --> 00:48:16,684
Did she go to a different cafe?

710
00:48:18,436 --> 00:48:19,521
Hello.

711
00:48:27,320 --> 00:48:28,905
I didn't know what to do with this.

712
00:48:31,324 --> 00:48:32,367
What is it?

713
00:48:36,496 --> 00:48:37,580
HAN DO-JIN

714
00:48:37,664 --> 00:48:38,915
LEE SEO-YOON

715
00:48:39,541 --> 00:48:41,084
Why didn't you throw them away?

716
00:48:41,167 --> 00:48:42,502
It's all personal information.

717
00:48:44,712 --> 00:48:46,047
And this is a new one.

718
00:48:47,215 --> 00:48:48,299
There's an audition soon.

719
00:48:48,383 --> 00:48:49,384
KIM JI-YUN

720
00:48:49,509 --> 00:48:51,845
So what? You want me to audition?

721
00:48:51,928 --> 00:48:53,388
You have nowhere to hide anymore.

722
00:48:54,931 --> 00:48:56,808
How is it to be known
as Son Jeong-a's son?

723
00:48:57,559 --> 00:48:59,853
How do you think? It sucks.

724
00:48:59,936 --> 00:49:01,271
Get famous, then.

725
00:49:01,354 --> 00:49:04,274
Make it so Jeong-a is known
as your mother.

726
00:49:04,357 --> 00:49:06,192
I don't want us to be known

727
00:49:07,277 --> 00:49:08,361
as mom and son, alright?

728
00:49:08,445 --> 00:49:09,487
Change your name, then.

729
00:49:09,571 --> 00:49:11,614
My name's Yong-min, so maybe Yong-seon?

730
00:49:12,073 --> 00:49:13,324
Come on.

731
00:49:13,825 --> 00:49:15,410
You're so childish.

732
00:49:15,493 --> 00:49:17,745
- Why is it so simple for you?
- It's not my life.

733
00:49:20,206 --> 00:49:22,375
So, are you two both into each other?

734
00:49:22,584 --> 00:49:23,585
Who?

735
00:49:26,087 --> 00:49:27,172
Ui-yeong?

736
00:49:27,630 --> 00:49:28,631
She's...

737
00:49:29,632 --> 00:49:31,259
She's just worried about me.

738
00:49:31,759 --> 00:49:33,386
She has someone else.

739
00:49:34,721 --> 00:49:36,222
He's about this tall

740
00:49:37,223 --> 00:49:38,349
and he's a CEO.

741
00:49:38,433 --> 00:49:39,434
So, you like her.

742
00:49:40,310 --> 00:49:41,728
Compassion's still a feeling.

743
00:49:41,895 --> 00:49:43,229
Who says you won't succeed

744
00:49:43,313 --> 00:49:45,231
if you try your best,
in acting and in love?

745
00:49:48,067 --> 00:49:49,944
KIM JI-YUN

746
00:49:55,116 --> 00:49:58,411
Sorry, I had to change our meeting place
because of a schedule change.

747
00:49:59,787 --> 00:50:02,790
Why did you want to see me?

748
00:50:04,459 --> 00:50:06,419
How was working at the hotel?

749
00:50:08,755 --> 00:50:10,423
I loved the work

750
00:50:10,507 --> 00:50:12,967
and my colleagues took
such great care of me.

751
00:50:13,134 --> 00:50:15,345
That's why I'm so bummed
that I'm not there anymore.

752
00:50:15,428 --> 00:50:16,679
- Really?
- Yeah.

753
00:50:16,846 --> 00:50:18,223
- Here.
- Okay.

754
00:50:26,523 --> 00:50:31,653
And as you know,
I messed up in many different ways.

755
00:50:31,736 --> 00:50:35,907
That's great, because our company requires
a lot of messing up and breaking things.

756
00:50:35,990 --> 00:50:39,702
If you're not just interested
in working in Purchasing or at a hotel

757
00:50:40,119 --> 00:50:41,871
would you like to try working at HOME?

758
00:50:42,580 --> 00:50:43,581
What?

759
00:50:43,998 --> 00:50:45,041
Excuse me

760
00:50:46,417 --> 00:50:49,754
you're not supposed to talk so loud.
This is a library.

761
00:50:51,172 --> 00:50:52,632
Oh, sorry, Sua.

762
00:50:59,597 --> 00:51:00,848
Thank you.

763
00:51:12,944 --> 00:51:17,740
I didn't study architecture,
and I've never done any work in the field.

764
00:51:22,870 --> 00:51:24,872
But you have a good eye for things.

765
00:51:25,373 --> 00:51:27,292
Not many of my employees studied
architecture.

766
00:51:27,500 --> 00:51:29,335
They studied philosophy
and child education.

767
00:51:29,669 --> 00:51:31,004
That's what makes it more fun.

768
00:51:31,504 --> 00:51:33,631
This is the result
of all that working together.

769
00:51:53,651 --> 00:51:55,528
I'd love to work there.

770
00:51:55,778 --> 00:51:56,988
I'd love to!

771
00:52:01,993 --> 00:52:04,829
When can you start?
The sooner, the better for us.

772
00:52:04,912 --> 00:52:07,415
I could even start right now.

773
00:52:07,498 --> 00:52:09,000
- Right now?
- Yes, right now.

774
00:52:09,751 --> 00:52:11,753
Since we haven't signed a contract yet

775
00:52:11,836 --> 00:52:16,174
why don't you just study
the company's portfolio today?

776
00:52:16,257 --> 00:52:18,843
That'll show you what kind of work we do.

777
00:52:19,052 --> 00:52:20,053
That sounds good!

778
00:52:20,386 --> 00:52:21,387
Okay.

779
00:52:23,306 --> 00:52:24,349
Look at this.

780
00:52:25,058 --> 00:52:26,142
These blocks turn.

781
00:52:32,148 --> 00:52:33,566
Should we have a seat?

782
00:52:36,527 --> 00:52:37,570
Is it good?

783
00:52:42,367 --> 00:52:44,661
- Did you do all that?
- Yeah, we did.

784
00:52:47,830 --> 00:52:51,542
We processed every piece of wood here.

785
00:53:03,846 --> 00:53:05,223
Sir.

786
00:53:05,598 --> 00:53:07,058
- Could I get some to-go?
- Sure.

787
00:53:15,692 --> 00:53:18,111
Ui-yeong, there's an emergency.
Are you free tonight?

788
00:53:18,194 --> 00:53:19,195
An emergency?

789
00:53:20,113 --> 00:53:21,572
What emergency now?

790
00:53:30,998 --> 00:53:32,166
What are you doing?

791
00:53:32,250 --> 00:53:34,001
Can I come over after work?

792
00:53:37,171 --> 00:53:38,923
DID YOU HAVE LUNCH? I HAD A SANDWICH.
WHAT ARE YOU DOING? CAN I COME OVER?

793
00:53:41,926 --> 00:53:43,845
Why isn't he replying?

794
00:53:50,435 --> 00:53:52,520
Hello, is Mr. Shin Ji-su here?

795
00:53:59,569 --> 00:54:01,028
- Please mind the stairs.
- Okay.

796
00:54:12,123 --> 00:54:14,375
This way, please. Enjoy your dinner.

797
00:54:14,459 --> 00:54:15,501
Thank you.

798
00:54:36,230 --> 00:54:38,941
Hello, I'm Shin Ji-su.

799
00:54:40,318 --> 00:54:41,319
Huh?

800
00:54:42,069 --> 00:54:43,154
Nice place, right?

801
00:54:43,488 --> 00:54:47,325
I looked everywhere for a nice spot
so we could have a good time.

802
00:54:48,618 --> 00:54:50,244
What are you doing?

803
00:54:51,704 --> 00:54:53,164
Doesn't it feel like a first date?

804
00:54:53,414 --> 00:54:55,249
If this were our first time meeting

805
00:54:56,000 --> 00:54:58,211
would you have fallen for me?

806
00:54:59,504 --> 00:55:01,047
We don't have time for this.

807
00:55:01,130 --> 00:55:02,465
You said it was an emergency.

808
00:55:02,840 --> 00:55:04,091
I rushed over here!

809
00:55:04,175 --> 00:55:05,676
Yeah, it's an emergency.

810
00:55:05,885 --> 00:55:07,261
I'm seriously starving.

811
00:55:08,346 --> 00:55:09,597
You haven't eaten yet, right?

812
00:55:11,599 --> 00:55:13,059
No, I haven't.

813
00:55:14,477 --> 00:55:17,063
But it looks
like a really expensive restaurant.

814
00:55:17,271 --> 00:55:18,731
It's okay. Order what you want.

815
00:55:19,565 --> 00:55:20,983
I want to thank you

816
00:55:21,359 --> 00:55:23,611
and treat you to something good.

817
00:55:30,243 --> 00:55:31,702
This much for soup?

818
00:55:38,209 --> 00:55:41,462
I'll take the tomato pasta.

819
00:55:46,884 --> 00:55:47,927
Excuse me.

820
00:55:51,722 --> 00:55:52,807
Are you ready to order?

821
00:55:53,182 --> 00:55:55,351
- Yeah, we'll get one salad
- Okay.

822
00:55:55,434 --> 00:55:56,811
one tomato pasta

823
00:55:56,894 --> 00:55:59,939
one octopus, and one New York strip.

824
00:56:00,022 --> 00:56:02,233
- You okay with wine?
- What? Yeah.

825
00:56:05,987 --> 00:56:08,739
- We'll take one bottle of this.
- Okay.

826
00:56:08,823 --> 00:56:11,033
- Anything else?
- No, we're good.

827
00:56:23,212 --> 00:56:24,255
Here.

828
00:56:24,839 --> 00:56:25,840
Thanks.

829
00:56:42,064 --> 00:56:44,191
I've been thinking a lot about you.

830
00:56:45,610 --> 00:56:47,737
- Huh?
- I thought

831
00:56:48,362 --> 00:56:52,158
I should be honest with you
about everything.

832
00:56:52,992 --> 00:56:55,828
And I didn't want to waste any time
once I made up my mind.

833
00:56:58,748 --> 00:57:00,166
People keep saying

834
00:57:00,958 --> 00:57:03,794
I'm lucky with such good parents
after the word got out.

835
00:57:04,587 --> 00:57:05,838
Because my father's a doctor.

836
00:57:07,381 --> 00:57:09,425
But even with a doctor dad

837
00:57:10,134 --> 00:57:11,260
my mom...

838
00:57:13,888 --> 00:57:15,222
died of cancer.

839
00:57:20,645 --> 00:57:22,104
You know what family is like.

840
00:57:22,939 --> 00:57:24,774
You can't bear their pain for them

841
00:57:24,857 --> 00:57:26,525
but you don't let them give up easily.

842
00:57:29,362 --> 00:57:30,529
But my dad...

843
00:57:31,530 --> 00:57:33,032
became so distracted...

844
00:57:34,951 --> 00:57:37,536
that he never even checked in on my mom.

845
00:57:42,416 --> 00:57:44,710
Everyone says my mom died from cancer

846
00:57:46,420 --> 00:57:47,588
but it felt...

847
00:57:50,174 --> 00:57:51,884
like she died of a broken heart.

848
00:57:56,639 --> 00:57:58,140
So, once my mom passed away

849
00:58:00,059 --> 00:58:01,560
I left home at 19.

850
00:58:03,229 --> 00:58:05,231
I joined the theater troupe
because they offered

851
00:58:06,065 --> 00:58:07,191
food and a place to stay.

852
00:58:09,110 --> 00:58:10,152
I see.

853
00:58:12,029 --> 00:58:13,823
I was so angry.

854
00:58:16,200 --> 00:58:18,536
I vowed to myself
that I'd never fall in love.

855
00:58:21,872 --> 00:58:23,040
Never.

856
00:58:35,261 --> 00:58:36,262
Have a seat.

857
00:58:44,603 --> 00:58:46,188
They'll publish the article soon.

858
00:58:47,648 --> 00:58:50,943
We've decided to clear
all misunderstandings about us.

859
00:58:51,193 --> 00:58:53,529
She's made a big decision.

860
00:58:55,823 --> 00:58:58,284
"Misunderstandings"?
What are you going to say?

861
00:58:58,617 --> 00:58:59,618
We'll be honest.

862
00:59:04,623 --> 00:59:05,750
"I NEVER HID IT.
I JUST WANTED TO PROTECT HIM..."

863
00:59:05,833 --> 00:59:08,794
I'll explain that I met Ji-hun
as my doctor

864
00:59:08,878 --> 00:59:11,088
and that we started dating and got married

865
00:59:11,172 --> 00:59:13,215
after your mother passed,
so it wasn't cheating.

866
00:59:14,341 --> 00:59:16,093
I'll also clarify

867
00:59:16,177 --> 00:59:18,179
that I was
just one-sidedly supporting you.

868
00:59:21,557 --> 00:59:23,309
So, that's your truth?

869
00:59:25,311 --> 00:59:26,562
Is it the same for you, Dad?

870
00:59:27,104 --> 00:59:29,607
- Of course...
- Come on.

871
00:59:31,442 --> 00:59:32,526
You're still a kid.

872
00:59:32,610 --> 00:59:35,821
You're still hung up on the past.

873
00:59:36,072 --> 00:59:37,198
You think your mom...

874
00:59:44,872 --> 00:59:47,124
People will want to know about you
once the news is out.

875
00:59:47,374 --> 00:59:49,251
Reporters will chase you everywhere, too.

876
00:59:50,711 --> 00:59:52,963
Move abroad for school.
I'll cover the tuition.

877
00:59:58,594 --> 01:00:01,222
See? That's my truth.

878
01:00:02,515 --> 01:00:04,683
We're not a family
that helps each other thrive.

879
01:00:05,392 --> 01:00:07,269
We hurt and break each other.

880
01:00:07,353 --> 01:00:09,146
- Ji-su.
- Leave my name out.

881
01:00:09,230 --> 01:00:10,773
Don't write a single thing about me.

882
01:00:11,065 --> 01:00:13,192
I left the troupe,
and as for the sponsored money

883
01:00:14,068 --> 01:00:15,528
I'll work and pay you back.

884
01:00:17,113 --> 01:00:18,489
I'm not a part of this family.

885
01:00:19,115 --> 01:00:20,533
I left a long time ago.

886
01:00:21,992 --> 01:00:23,327
And I'll never be a part of it.

887
01:00:28,124 --> 01:00:29,125
Ji-su...

888
01:00:31,210 --> 01:00:34,046
I see why your acting's like that.
You don't question anything.

889
01:00:34,505 --> 01:00:37,883
Love that makes you numb
to someone else's pain.

890
01:00:38,384 --> 01:00:39,510
Isn't it disgusting?

891
01:00:41,095 --> 01:00:42,555
You've killed a person...

892
01:00:44,181 --> 01:00:45,516
with that noble love of yours.

893
01:01:00,865 --> 01:01:01,907
That...

894
01:01:03,075 --> 01:01:04,410
must've been so difficult.

895
01:01:07,496 --> 01:01:08,956
You did well to stay strong.

896
01:01:15,671 --> 01:01:16,672
Yeah.

897
01:01:23,554 --> 01:01:26,348
This is all the wood we salvaged
from the rain that night.

898
01:01:26,432 --> 01:01:30,477
We have to start cutting them tomorrow,
so order what we couldn't save.

899
01:01:30,644 --> 01:01:31,645
Okay.

900
01:01:32,479 --> 01:01:34,148
Gosh.

901
01:01:36,859 --> 01:01:38,235
Does my arm smell?

902
01:01:39,236 --> 01:01:40,696
Yeah, just a bit.

903
01:01:41,655 --> 01:01:43,490
Sua's telling you to shower.

904
01:01:44,033 --> 01:01:45,159
I showered twice.

905
01:01:45,242 --> 01:01:47,077
Why are you here? You should be resting.

906
01:01:47,661 --> 01:01:50,122
I told you guys to go home, too.
Don't stay here so late.

907
01:01:50,206 --> 01:01:51,540
Come on.

908
01:01:51,749 --> 01:01:54,960
You said woodworking professionals
shouldn't be so emotional.

909
01:01:55,377 --> 01:01:57,588
Why do you look so scared?

910
01:01:58,255 --> 01:01:59,590
You know what we always say.

911
01:01:59,673 --> 01:02:02,343
"We don't get many sunny days
for woodworking during the year."

912
01:02:02,635 --> 01:02:07,056
"Wood is vulnerable in water and fire
so the person handling it must be strong."

913
01:02:07,139 --> 01:02:10,226
I have to keep telling myself that
because it's so tough.

914
01:02:11,143 --> 01:02:14,563
Oh, right, I hired a newbie.
She'll join us soon.

915
01:02:14,647 --> 01:02:16,565
I'm not sure if you'll have much less work

916
01:02:16,649 --> 01:02:18,067
but I have high hopes.

917
01:02:18,275 --> 01:02:19,860
- Treat her well.
- Really?

918
01:02:20,486 --> 01:02:21,695
A newbie! It's been forever!

919
01:02:21,779 --> 01:02:23,072
Is everyone done eating?

920
01:02:23,155 --> 01:02:26,492
The last one to leave the office
has to clean it tomorrow!

921
01:02:28,202 --> 01:02:30,329
I have to pack up!

922
01:02:30,412 --> 01:02:31,622
- Oh, no!
- Gosh!

923
01:02:31,997 --> 01:02:33,666
- Bye!
- Wait!

924
01:02:34,208 --> 01:02:36,043
- Hey!
- Hey! Clean this up!

925
01:02:36,126 --> 01:02:37,586
Clean it first! Hey!

926
01:02:37,670 --> 01:02:38,754
Bye!

927
01:02:44,009 --> 01:02:45,469
Are you home, Ui-yeong?

928
01:02:45,886 --> 01:02:47,763
Can I see you if I head over now?

929
01:02:53,185 --> 01:02:54,228
Let's...

930
01:02:55,854 --> 01:02:56,855
just go.

931
01:03:03,946 --> 01:03:05,239
How was the steak?

932
01:03:05,531 --> 01:03:07,241
It was good.

933
01:03:15,499 --> 01:03:16,500
Well, here we are.

934
01:03:17,293 --> 01:03:19,295
I'll head in now. Get home safely.

935
01:03:20,045 --> 01:03:21,547
I still have something to tell you.

936
01:03:21,672 --> 01:03:23,173
Oh, what is it?

937
01:03:23,590 --> 01:03:25,718
You know how you told me
to stand for what I loved?

938
01:03:28,095 --> 01:03:29,179
I like you.

939
01:03:32,266 --> 01:03:35,269
- Huh?
- I know I'm not that great right now.

940
01:03:35,936 --> 01:03:37,730
But I'm going to take acting seriously.

941
01:03:37,938 --> 01:03:39,481
I have an audition booked

942
01:03:39,565 --> 01:03:41,233
and I'll keep trying until I get hired.

943
01:03:44,028 --> 01:03:46,572
- Ji-su...
- I'll dress well around you

944
01:03:47,281 --> 01:03:49,408
so that I don't embarrass you.

945
01:03:49,658 --> 01:03:52,870
I'll also move to a nice place
where you can come visit.

946
01:03:53,787 --> 01:03:55,956
I can't take you
to a fancy restaurant often

947
01:03:56,206 --> 01:03:58,375
but I promise to take you to one

948
01:03:59,418 --> 01:04:00,461
for big celebrations.

949
01:04:05,049 --> 01:04:06,175
I want...

950
01:04:08,844 --> 01:04:10,220
to fall in love with you.

951
01:04:16,018 --> 01:04:17,478
Oh, I...

952
01:04:22,358 --> 01:04:23,400
Tae-seop.

953
01:04:47,216 --> 01:04:50,094
THE PRACTICAL GUIDE TO LOVE

954
01:04:52,471 --> 01:04:55,099
DATING IS DIFFERENT NOW

955
01:04:59,561 --> 01:05:02,606
2,380 STEPS OUT OF 8,000

956
01:05:06,944 --> 01:05:10,406
IT'S ROMANTIC WHEN YOU DO IT WITH SOMEONE

957
01:05:15,411 --> 01:05:18,122
STAND FOR WHAT YOU LOVE

958
01:05:18,539 --> 01:05:20,916
YOU DID WELL TO STAY STRONG

959
01:05:23,127 --> 01:05:26,839
Who would possibly imagine
that this would happen on a blind date?

960
01:05:27,131 --> 01:05:28,549
- Ui-yeong!
- Hey!

961
01:05:28,632 --> 01:05:30,884
I've never seen a player in such a dilemma

962
01:05:30,968 --> 01:05:33,011
with both options in her hands.

963
01:05:33,137 --> 01:05:35,681
I'm not even close
to leaning toward one over the other.

964
01:05:36,849 --> 01:05:38,142
Hey, your shirt is unbuttoned.

965
01:05:38,225 --> 01:05:40,144
- I unbuttoned it on purpose.
- What?

966
01:05:40,227 --> 01:05:42,062
I couldn't stop thinking about you,
so here I am.

967
01:05:42,187 --> 01:05:43,730
Don't just think about it alone.

968
01:05:43,814 --> 01:05:45,649
You'll have moments where you become sure

969
01:05:46,108 --> 01:05:47,901
when you spend more time together.

970
01:05:47,985 --> 01:05:49,361
You just need to be more sure of yourself.

971
01:05:50,612 --> 01:05:52,072
I'll wait for you.

972
01:05:57,870 --> 01:05:59,872
Subtitles by: Min-sun Kim
